comment:
This video clearly indicates that JD is human, & relatable, while obviously 100% non-violent towards people. The defendant's argument that it is a thin line between hitting an inanimate object and a living being is an asinine statement. The defendant themselves have shown that JD vents his frustration & anger in a completely non-threatening manner.
If this video was intended to be AH's smoking gun, it failed miserably. 
This is not proof of a violent individual... this is proof that:
A. At his 'craziest', JD merely pours a large glass of wine. This is as crazy as he gets during a moment of extreme personal anguish. 
B. At his 'craziest', he exits the room without any hint of physical aggression. He says "Bye" & leaves.
C. AH audibly chuckles & appears as cool as a cucumber. She is clearly not someone that feared for her life, as repeatedly stated in her deposition. 
I truly hope that the judge watches this video several times. It is a perfect example of being a fly on the wall during a very tense situation & shows JD's reaction. 
If this case is reliant on 'He said/She said' evidence, then let the record show that he said "Bye"... and then walked away without raising a finger.

comment:
Poor Johnny, a loving wife or partner should never film their spouse when they are in such a vulnerable state.

Johnny did say AH was building up a dossier on him all this time. That's not love in my opinion. The photos of Johnny Depp showing him passed out with icecream down his leg that someone else could have easily placed also proved that he was being manipulated and treated badly.

People take out their anger, pain and frustration on inanimate objects all the time. Many choose to do this by taking up a hobby like going to a gym, boxing or yoga, even screaming out whilst your alone can be therapeutic. Unfortunatly sometimes you dont always have access to a better constructive way to let all your problems go. Johnny slammed a few cupboards.. doesnt make him an abuser.

The original cut version was left for interpretation, many wondering what happened next, but now we know Johnny did what he said hes always done. He walked away. Proving once again he being very credible. When  actions speak louder than words it's nice when your words back up your actions.

Johnny proves once again that hes not an abuser. I am glad that they showed the whole version of this on the last day of court. It was the last mic drop during the final statement. In court they showed the cut version a lot apprently, that means they were deliberately hiding things, they purposly cut out Amber smirking and giggling and Johnny walking away. I hope the judge recognises this and it goes in Johnny Depps favour.
